# Klipper Configuration Files

## Modular Include System

Variant entry files (`Xplorer_*.cfg`) compose the full config by including fragments:

```
Xplorer_SINGLE.cfg
  ├── Xp_Xplorer_Vars.cfg        # shared variables
  ├── Xp_Basic_Settings.cfg       # core printer setup
  ├── Xp_Tool0.cfg                # extruder/tool definition
  ├── Xp_X_Axis_SINGLE.cfg        # variant-specific axis
  ├── Xp_Y_Axis_1xGantry.cfg      # gantry config
  ├── Xp_Z_Axis.cfg               # Z stepper + tilt
  ├── Xp_Macros_*.cfg             # GCode macros (Base + variant + per-tool)
  ├── Xp_SmartSensor_T0.cfg       # filament sensor
  ├── Xp_Calibrate_offsets_*.cfg  # tool offset calibration
  ├── Xp_PLR_*.cfg                # power loss recovery
  ├── Xp_Shell_Commands_*.cfg     # shell command wrappers
  └── Xp_Mainsail.cfg             # Mainsail UI integration
```

## Syntax Rules

- Klipper INI-style syntax: `[section_name]` headers, `key: value` or `key = value` pairs
- Comments use `#` (often `##` for section headers)
- Section visual separators: `##################################` or `##################################################################`
- GCode macros use Jinja2 templating: `{% if %}`, `{ printer.* }`, `{ params.* }`

## Key Patterns

- Each variant has its own `[z_tilt]` points and `[bed_mesh]` config
- Tool definitions go in `Xp_Tool<N>.cfg` (V1.0) or `Xp_V1.1_Tool<N>.cfg` (V1.1)
- Variables stored in `[gcode_macro _SENSOR_*_VARIABLES]` or `[gcode_macro _XPLORER_VARIABLES]`
- `[save_variables]` writes to `variables.cfg` on the printer

## When Editing

- Preserve the `[include ...]` order — Klipper processes them sequentially
- Keep variant-specific settings in the correct variant file, not in shared fragments
- Test changes against all affected variants (SINGLE, IDEX, 2xGANTRY, IQEX)
